reviews_data.review_text: It was quite.   Most libraries are not.  Folks talking loud on phones...  Children running around like they're on playground.   As I was exiting, a older Lady was  Being disrespectful to Security.....   And she was loud because,  he told her no phone calls inside.

This THU 24jul2025 morning, i went to the Charlotte Mecklenburg Library to "re-work" on my NC_AHCD "paperwork" cos those i did yesterday, on my home (~10 y.o.) Brother Laser Printer/Scanner; its scannings, conversion to PDF, and printouts were "blurry" poor quality.
Bte, its been many years since i'd been to a public library. As such, i am so out-of-touch .. "obsolete" about computers and technology,
Well, i seek help from the Librarian on how to use their (public shared-use) computers, printer/scanner/copier .. 😅
Lucky for me, the Librarian was professional, friendly and nice. And she kindly "hand-held" worked with me, "step-by-step" for my scannings, copying, PDF to email, etc .. Thank you much Librarian 🙏
Awesome staff!

Sugar Creek Library has the most welcoming staff ! They're always smiling when we walk in, and so helpful with anything we ask. They explain things to make it understandable. The events there are interesting ~ wish I could go way more !

Nasty 🤮 and dirty is an understatement, the first computer I was sitting at had so many hairs and dirt all over it! Staff were rude when I approached them to tell them about it! My 2nd computer was do nasty I was scared to sit down I ask staff was they available to clean the area she walked off and approach another co-worker and came back and handed me some wet wipes… I replied so you want me to clean after someone else without gloves on? I don’t work here! Which I thought was very unprofessional! I was ask did I want to sit somewhere else but the whole computer area look nasty and not clean! Always greeted by homeless.. Right now my office is down and I needed to print a few things off….. who is in charge of cleaning the libraries I’m just curious?
a nice place to hang out and read or just to get some work done

small not much of a selection. Encountered some very rude and disrespectful people outside on the way in and out limited parking had to do a couple circles to find parking. First time coming here but I think I'll find another location after these books are returned.
Helpful
The catalog was down for maintenance in the middle of the day which I found annoying but the employees were pleasant and attentive.
The vibe was lovely. And the staff was so warm. We will come back to read or hangout

Great workers, they have been so kind and welcoming to my Daisy and I ❣️... After I had shown Daisy's Service registration we have only been welcomed.... I prefer Sugar Creek Library than any of the others in Charlotte.

What  a wonderful summer afternoon treat! I even came across some really helpful information at the Block Party. And its fun library for children without dealing with uptown traffic to get to Imaginon
Good
Quiet, not crowded. Nice community library.
Never busy.
Although the library is a little small, the staff members are wonderful.
Great Plant Adopt event with Tonya!
reviews_data.owner_answer: Thank you for attending our plant adoption event, Eve!

reviews_data.review_text: Came here for the first time today, I usually go to the one off university but decided to do a location switch for some new scenery. So glad I came here! Staff was super friendly and the library is very spacious and quiet, lots of natural lighting from the high windows, and bathrooms were very clean too! I also loved that it is right beside the police station and also has an on sight security guard. I will definitely be coming here more often.
Very helpful staff, could have a better inventory of materials on site
I always love goin to the sugar creek branch where they’re always so helpful and courteous. Thank you so much for your patience with me.🙂
Staff/volunteers are very accommodating,helpful and friendly.
As always they were so acommodating. Free copies and everything.! Glad to have our libraries open again!

Howie is the best!! I told him what kind of books I was looking for, and be that COVID is going on no one could go into the library..but howie pick me out some great books on what I was looking for!! Thanks a lot!!!!! Excellent customer service!!
Was able to get services while in pandemic mode fast and quick services

Incredibly unfortunate to have such a nice library paired with awful customer service. To deny someone the ability to check out something simply because you wish to close early (when you admit that the person has clearly arrived before you close) is a perfect example of why libraries have such difficulty maintaining funding these days. Save your time and effort and visit another branch that actually cares about you.
Very helpful and respectful. Love coming here.
Poor selection of books by African American authors. Such a paradox considering the neighborhood this library serves...

I love this library because the staff are always helpful and kind. The library is always clean and there is always a computer available. I would like it if libraries would provide wipes for the computers to cut down on the spread of germs, but they don't. I carry my own wipes into the library and wipe down the keyboard and mouse for my own protection. I hope they can start offering these things in the future. I have even asked for a wipe before and was given one. Amazing staff there and I would recommend this library to all. Happy Holidays and best wishes for the New Year!
This library, along with all the Charlotte libraries I’ve visited, is wonderful. I love how the city clearly invests in the resources they offer us. These libraries truly are a blessing
I love my library!
Perfect location and extremely convenient.
Very friendly staff
No complaints, the staff are very friendly and helpful. Cleainess in the restroom and entire building excellent. I really enjoy the quiet environment
Best service possible for all books lover

This review is for the WiFi connection at this particular branch.  I don't know what the issue is at THIS branch...but the wifi is painfully slow.  Speedtest isn't even registering .08 Mbps and this has been the case multiple times I've been here.    I have to end up using my cellphone connection as a hotspot.   The wifi speed isn't particularly fast at the other branches, but it is at least usable.  Not the case at the Sugar Creek Branch.  Wifi slower than dial-up.

This library is very little, and story time for kids is boring :) I would recommend to choose other branch. Plaza Midwood branch is much better than this one. Although the staff is friendly and really helpful
Pretty big library.  Never busy.
The best place to be
